    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-06-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-06-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="253"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d253">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Goodnow</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Cridler</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Consulate-General of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-06-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 29, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 270.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Continuing my 269, this date, I have received
                    to-day from Consul Gracey, Foochow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Have consulted regarding protection for three weeks past. Instruct if
                            anything more contemplated. All quiet.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>This carries out the statement in my No. 265 that you have now authorized what
                    circumstances has compelled us to do without direct authority.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Goodnow</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                            >Consul-General.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
